\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 79. C. ipsaria} Stoj. & Kitanov,{\i  Bull. Soc. Bot. Bulg.}{\b  9}: 102(1943). Like {\b 78}({\b c}) but stems 8-20 cm; involucre c. 10 mm; appendages yellowish- or purplish-brown, with hyaline auricles at base; pappus as long as achene.{\i  Rock-crevices. • N. Aegean region} ({\i Thasos}). Gr.
\par

\par

