\pard\f0\fs28    ({\b a}) Subsp. {\b rutifolia}: Stems 20-40 cm, corymbosely branched. Lower leaves 1-pinnatisect; cauline with sessile, spathulate segments. Involucre c. 12 × 6 mm, ovoid-cylindrical; bracts subtomentose; appendages pale brown, with 3-5 fimbriae on each side, the apex not pungent. Pappus ¼ as long as achene.{\i  Stony slopes. E. part of Balkan peninsula}.
\par

\pard\f0\fs28    ({\b b}) Subsp. {\b jurineifolia} (Boiss.) Nyman, {\i Consp.} 425 (1879) ({\i C. jurineifolia} Boiss.): Stems 30-80 cm, paniculately branched. Lower leaves 2-pinnatisect; cauline with shortly petiolate, spathulate segments. Involucre 12-13 × 6-7 mm, oblong-ovoid; bracts glabrous; appendages rather dark brown, with 3-6 fimbriae on each side, the apex pungent. Pappus very short or absent. {\i Scrub slopes. Bulgaria and Romania.}
\par

\pard\f0\fs28    ({\b c}) Subsp. {\b pseudobovina} (Hayek) Dostál,{\i  Bot. Jour. Linn. Soc.}{\b  71}: 196 (1976) ({\i C. pseudobovina} Hayek): Like subsp. ({\b b}) but cauline leaves with linear-lanceolate segments; involucre c. 10 × 6 mm, narrowly ovoid; bracts sometimes sparsely tomentose; appendages pale brown, with 5-7 fimbriae on each side; pappus absent.{\i  Grassy slopes. N. Bulgaria}.
\par

